History.Prophecy:
Martek began (or rather, resumed) preparations shortly after capturing Khalitharius, penning a prophecy that the efreet would be released a thousand years from then, and his Sphere of Power would be required in order to save Raurin from the efreet's rampage.

He gave the efreet's prison to the Lord of [[Pazar]], along with the [[Star of Aga-Pelar]] as payment for keeping the genie imprisoned.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|96}}{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|107}} and the pillar at the center of the city to deliver a message about it.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|100}}

He also teleported to the [[Citadel of Ice and Steel]] in the [[Elemental Plane of Air]], where in an audience with the Caliph of all [[djinn]] he convinced his Vizier, [[Aeraldoth]], to allow himself to be bound for a thousand years to do battle with the efreet once the latter was released. Martek bound the genie in a bottle, which he concealed in [[Phoenix (city)|Phoenix]].{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|86}} The wizard had created a bottle that required a magical word in order to release its captive; using his magic, he made a mark that would appear on the palm of the bride of the Sheik's son in the [[Oasis of the White Palm]].{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|93}} He also created two amulets, which he gave to the Sheik and his son; those amulets, when combined with the bride's palm, would form a message on how to release the djinn.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|62}}{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|80}}{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|84}} He hid the final Star-Gem, the [[Star of Khan-Pelar]], in the [[Temple of Set]] beneath the Oasis of the White Palm,{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|74}} alongside a bone scroll case with a map inside it.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|78}} Furthermore, he placed a message on a shrine atop the Temple of Set.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|72}}

At the time of his final retreat, there were only two trials in Martek's Citadel that had yet to be completed: the Black Abyss and the Mobius' Tower.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|109}} Considering his preparations complete, he had his remains displayed in the citadel, thereafter the [[Tomb of Martek]].{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|108}}
